data.description: Special Note: Buyer's agents are welcomed at a 3% commission. GORGEOUS custom Swiss Chalet!  Rare-level entry, four-story, two-car garage with million-dollar lake views in beautiful Lake Arrowhead, California. This home has hardwood floors, Austrian imported chandeliers, a custom-built stone fireplace, comes fully furnished, a full-length deck off the living room, two full-size glass sliding doors with A-frame windows above, custom double pained windows throughout, glass door framed kitchen pantry, granite countertops, all stainless steel appliances included (brand new quiet dishwasher), upgraded sink shower/tub faucets, powder room 1/2 bath at entryway, loft/bedroom with closet and private restroom. Third-floor bedrooms accessed by stairway near the front door, oversized master bedroom with dual closets and private bathroom.  Second bedroom has a ceiling fan and mountain views. The third downstairs bedroom comes furnished with a double guest bed, stacked bunk beds, and shared full bathroom with tub/shower combination. Workshop and bonus/game room are accessed from an outside side staircase. The game room is fully finished, carpeted, and comes furnished with a couch, love seat, free-standing popcorn maker, corner desk, pool table, bookshelf, half bathroom with wooden floors, a set of windows on either side of the room and overhead lighting. The two car garage has an electronc garage door opener, overhead full length shelving, room for parking for two vehicles on the front deck and two cars in the garage, quiet dead end street with friendly neighbors on either side, roads maintained by Lake Arrowhead Villas Mutual Services who also provide clean and plentiful water. The famous Tudor House is located within 5 minutes walking distance where you can enjoy delicious Sunday brunches and seasonal plays. The Lake Arrowhead Village is a five-minute driving distance away where you will find a variety of restaurants, clothing shops, and a supermarket. Santa's Village/Sky Park is five minutes' driving distance and Snow Valley Ski lifts in Running Springs are 22 minutes away. Once again, buyer agents are welcome.
data.whatILove: We especially enjoy waking up each morning, grabbing a cup of coffee or tea, and taking in the beautiful lake views from the large glass sliding door windows or in warmer weather sitting on the deck and hearing the blue jays and squirrels chirping away at each other in a game of hide and seek of the oak nuts. In the fall, Dogwood trees just below the back deck are an added treat as they provide us with beautiful orange and red leaves. In the winter after an overnight snowfall, we enjoy looking out over the snowy landscape to the lake and distant snow-capped mountains. Off the back deck is a majestic 70-foot-tall Douglas fir tree which eagles, woodpeckers, and blue jays love to perch on as they overlook the valley. We think you will be just as taken as we were the first time we stood on the deck and took in the beautiful Lake Arrowhead valley that was spread out before us.
